<|startoftext|>Headline:"Trump says will not rule out selling country, says time to strike deals"
Content: "WASHINGTON (Reuters) - U.S. President Donald Trump said on Tuesday he would not rule out selling the United States the country, saying when the time to negotiate came he was going to go to Japan. In comments that drew a swift condemnation from the Japanese foreign minister and a wave of blank stares, Trump said: “As of today - and the day before - I’m not in such a position.” His remarks came as he and his Japanese counterpart Shinzo Abe, who is scheduled to arrive in Washington later this week for bilateral meetings, will hold their first day meeting. The two leaders met at the White House last month after their first face-to-face conversation. Asked by reporters after arriving in the United States to whether he had ruled out that it would be possible he could sell a U.S. embassy if Democrats failed to accept a presidential election to clean up corruption, Trump said: “There will be a deal.”  The United States has faced a host of questions from international and domestic authorities about whether a new Trump administration would pursue a diplomatic solution to address the crisis. Asked by reporters at his first official visit to the White House about whether he would have a discussion about selling the U.S. embassy to Japan, Trump said: “That’s kind of a tough one,” before adding it would be a bad idea to sell the embassy. “It’s going to make it hard to negotiate,” he said.      ",<|endoftext|>
